cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for evaluating machine learning models by systematically exploring the input data space to identify weaknesses. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments are conducted on ShapeNet object classification, which is a computer vision task, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely category. The use of an adversarial examiner also suggests a potential connection to adversarial attacks, which is covered by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes using the identified weaknesses to improve the model in the next iteration, which could be related to neural architecture search, covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
